dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy c Bailey b McKay 16 (37b 2x4 0x6 43m) SR: 43.24

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket! Here comes the wicket. Short of length on off and middle, Sammy tries to flick it to the leg side , but the ball gets big on him and it takes a leading edge. dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c Thomas b Holder 10 (6b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: Mr DRS has been called into service. It was short of length outside off, the batsman stays in the crease and tries to flay his bat at that, it takes an outside edge, seemingly so, (I heard a noise), but the umpire says no. Being reviewed...Yes, it is out. Although it didn't show up clearly on the hot-spot, the noise was too loud to ignore. Holder 1 - hot-spot 0

commentPreTextItems.html: Austen: "Maxwell is scoring runs for fun, I bet Khawaja is having a right old time watching him bat!"

commentTextItems.html: comes forward, plays a soft push to the offside and completes a quick single to hand out a big thrashing to the tourists

commentPostTextItems.html: That brings us to the end of our coverage. It has been a short and sweet day. I will be back on Sunday on comms, hoping for a better contest. Here is Dan Brettig's match-report. This is Devashish Fuloria signing off for the day. Ciao

Michael Clarke: "It is nice to be on the other side after what happened in Brisbane. I think this was a very nice Test match wicket and that was the reason we would have wanted to bowl first anyway. Mitchell Johnson is the only other bowler I have seen do what Starc did today. It was the total which prompted us to send Maxwell up the order. If Maxwell bats like this, he can certainly have opening every game [smiles]. We are going to enjoy tonight and will get ready for a tough game in two days time. It is going to be a better batting wicket on Sunday"

Darren Sammy: "They hit us hard, and now we need to hit them hard in the next game. Hopefully it was just a one off. The team backed itself to bat first. But we fell to seam and swing. We need to come back strong and hard in two days time."

Mitchell Starc gets a fancy something in a box because he is the player of the match: "It is nice when the ball swings. It's nice when you get rhythm like that. If you had put enough ball in the right areas, the pitch had enough to help the bowlers."

Game over within 10 overs. It is like Super Mario found a pipeline to take him close to the finish. Clarke walks out to shake hands along with his teammates. Maxwell came out and had some fun, he missed some, but he found the range with some unorthodox hitting. But the real star of the match was Mitch Starc. What a spell he bowled earlier today? If you haven't seen it, I recommend the highlights highly.

Gareth: "Years ago Australia A gave Sri Lanka such a hiding on a tour, that the game was over within the first innings time frame. They then played a 25 over exhibition match to make sure the crowd got their money's worth. I hope they do that hear tonight as well!"
Super Ted: "@ Gareth - I somehow don't think the boys will be allowed to play an exhibition in this day and age! #rotationpolicy"
Bill: "@Gareth They don't think of the crowd anymore. They won't want to risk injury or give the West Indians extra batting practice."
Arpit: "These type of matches are surely eating up the TV commercial revenue for boards. ICC should come up with some kind of rule about it too"
David: "At least the WI batsmen can console themselves with the knowledge that they managed the 2nd, 3rd and 4th highest individual scores in the match (extras aside)."

commentPreTextItems.html: Davinder: "Despite a poor performance from WI, Jason Holder has decent debut." He is coming round the wicket to Uzzie

commentTextItems.html: short of length wide outside off, moves away after passing the batsman who has left it alone
flighted delivery on off and middle, he comes forward to push it to the leg side, but misses as the ball turns and hits the pads

headshotImage.caption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: short of length delivery, quick too, defended back to the bowler off the back foot
fifty for Maxwell as he cuts it hard through gully on the off side
he goes down the leg side and is called a wide, Maxwell wanted to send it to deep backward square
that is more orthodox stuff, flighted delivery is smashed over the off side, inside out

commentPreTextItems.html: Where is going now..? Let's see, deep square leg i say.

commentTextItems.html: no he goes the other way with a reverse sweep, but makes no connection
spins away after pitching outside off, Uzzie cuts it to point, who misfields allowing a single
he shuffles across the stumps, not as animatedly as earlier, and misses the short of length delivery down the leg side.

headshotImage.caption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Usman Khawaja player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: charges out and gets a full swinging delivery outside off, misses it
one bounce, two bounce, and it is a boundary over extra cover. What sort of short is that. He hammers this rising delivery from around his chest with a swat over cover
now goes all the way across to the off side, trying to paddle that over short fine, makes not connection

commentPreTextItems.html: Barry Stump: "Won't be going to the next match at the WACA - there's going to be a lot of beer sitting in the sun after this show!"

commentTextItems.html: and tries to send this one down to downtown Perth by moving his front leg out of the way, the ball  comes in with the angles and goes between bat and pad
moves to the leg side, but the ball is full and it takes an inside edge to square leg
flighted on middle and leg, it grips and turns past the bat. Uzzie beaten outside off

commentPostTextItems.html: David: "Khawaja's gone past his highest score in ODI's ... what an achievement!"

commentTextItems.html: 93 ks, flat and quick on off, he comes forward an defends

commentPreTextItems.html: Dale: "As glad i am to see Australia be on the right side of an embarrasing total, i am still a bit dissapointed the new batsmen didn't get a real chance to prove themselves."

commentTextItems.html: short and spins away from Uzzie, who uses the opportunity and cuts it hard past point to pick some welcome runs
comes down the pitch, but the ball is flatter, he has to dab it to cover for a single
and goes for a power sweep off a flighted one, but hits the man at forward short leg. It hit the fielder on his shin pads

dismissalComment.html: take this one then!! Full inswinging delivery outside off, Polly doesn't get too far forward and chops the ball back to the stumps. That's out twice in two balls in my book.
No. 5 for Mister Starc! Length ball on middle and leg, swings in. Mr. Holder had moved outside leg stump to send this over the bowler's head, but he misses and loses the leg-stump.

caught my Mr. Clarke at you know where! As simple as you like. Length delivery on off stump, moves a touch away after pitching and Bravo plays that from the back foot when probably he should have been forward, the ball takes a proper edge and goes straight to first slip

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c Thomas b Holder 10 (6b 1x4 0x6 18m) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: Mr DRS has been called into service. It was short of length outside off, the batsman stays in the crease and tries to flay his bat at that, it takes an outside edge, seemingly so, (I heard a noise), but the umpire says no. Being reviewed...Yes, it is out. Although it didn't show up clearly on the hot-spot, the noise was too loud to ignore. Holder 1 - hot-spot 0
